"'''A Day to Celebrate'''" was a song created by the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiees]] of [[Kashyyyk/Legends|Kashyyyk]] as a celebratory hymn for [[Life Day/Legends|Life Day]]. It allowed Wookiees who couldn't attend their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] to celebrate in some small way, wherever they happened to be.

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref>{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=152583&start=870#15778940|thread=Holocron continuity database questions|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-10-12|time=6:13 PM|quote=Wookiee Life Day occurs every 3 years, one of which fell at ~1.5 ABY.}}</ref> [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] sang this song for everyone in attendance at the [[Tree of Life/Legends|Tree of Life]].<ref name="SWHS" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|The show ends with a tearful reunion with Chewbacca and family. Everyone gathers round as Carrie Fisher sings the Life Day song. This is pure torture, not because Fisher can't sing, but because it's so schmaltzy. Lyrics set to the tune of the ''Star Wars'' theme? Yeecchh!|[[Jon Bradley Snyder]]|<ref name="The Star Wars Holiday Special (article)">{{InsiderCite|23|The Star Wars Holiday Special (article)|''The Star Wars Holiday Special''}}</ref>}}
"A Day to Celebrate" was performed by [[Carrie Fisher]] in ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. It features lyrics written by [[Ken Welch|Ken]] and [[Mitzie Welch]], set to a rearranged version of the [[Star Wars Main Title|''Star Wars'' main theme]] by [[John Williams]].<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.starwarsholidayspecial.com/text/production_notes.htm|text=Official Production Notes|archivedate=20171119191722}}</ref> According to writer [[Bruce Vilanch]], Fisher insisted on being able to sing in the ''Holiday Special'', and even performed a few songs for him on piano.<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/magazine/2008/12/star_wars_special200812|text=The Han Solo Comedy Hour!|author=DiGiacomo, Frank|date=2008-12-22|work=[[Wikipedia:Vanity Fair|Vanity Fair]]|archivedate=20180621143534}}</ref> The original recording of the song was featured on a CD included with the 2007 book ''[[The Star Wars Vault]]''.<ref name="I Have a Bad Feeling About This!">{{InsiderCite|106|I Have a Bad Feeling About This!}}</ref>

